\title{biparty: Congressional Bipartisanship Scores by Member and Issue Area}
\description{
\code{biparty} provides Congressional Bipartisanship Scores (CBS) for all
members of the U.S. House and Senate from 1983 to 2024, spanning the 98th
through the 118th Congresses. The scores are introduced and described in
Dobson and Lollis (2026), with support from the Portman Center for Policy
Solutions at the University of Cincinnati. The package was developed by
Mackenzie R. Dobson, Assistant Professor of Political Science at the
University of Tennessee, Knoxville, and Jacob M. Lollis, Assistant Professor
of Political Science at the University of Cincinnati.
}
\details{
The package provides two datasets:
\itemize{
\item \link{aggregate.cbs} - overall attract and offer scores per member,
  Congress, and chamber, with identifier crosswalk columns included.
\item \link{issue.area.cbs} - the same scores computed separately within each
  of 34 CRS major policy areas, with identifier crosswalk columns included.
}

Scores range from 0 to 1, with higher scores indicating more cross-party
activity, and are constructed from more than 2.4 million cosponsorship
decisions on 147,669 bills. The \emph{attract} score measures the share of
out-party original cosponsors on bills the member sponsored; the \emph{offer}
score measures the share of the member's own original cosponsorships that
went to out-party sponsors. Both measures are available in raw and
precision-weighted variants. The weighted version adjusts for imprecise
measurement associated with legislators with low bill activity, pulling
low-volume observations toward a Congress x chamber (or Congress x chamber
x issue) prior mean.

Key functions:
\itemize{
\item \code{\link[=get_member_scores]{get_member_scores()}} - look up a single member's scores.
\item \code{\link[=rank_members]{rank_members()}} - leaderboard of members by score.
\item \code{\link[=compare_members]{compare_members()}} - side-by-side comparison of two or more members.
\item \code{\link[=get_state_delegation]{get_state_delegation()}} - scores for an entire state delegation.
\item \code{\link[=get_congress_summary]{get_congress_summary()}} - Congress-level summary statistics.
\item \code{\link[=get_issue_scores]{get_issue_scores()}} - all members' scores for a single policy area.
\item \code{\link[=get_issue_trend]{get_issue_trend()}} - issue-area bipartisanship trends over time.
\item \code{\link[=list_issues]{list_issues()}} - enumerate available CRS issue area labels.
\item \code{\link[=plot_bipartisanship]{plot_bipartisanship()}} - violin plot of issue-area scores by party and chamber.
\item \code{\link[=plot_trend]{plot_trend()}} - time-series line chart of scores across Congresses.
\item \code{\link[=plot_member_profile]{plot_member_profile()}} - bar chart of a member's issue-area score profile.
}
}
